      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/42041.Max_Weber">About Max Weber</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/42041.Max_Weber"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1630864117p3/42041.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/42041.Max_Weber">Max Weber
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
697
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer2247731681364564938">(Arabic: <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/7862079._' rel='nofollow noopener'>ماكس فيبر</a>)<br/><br/>Maximilian Carl Emil Weber was a German lawyer, politician, historian, sociologist and political economist, who profoundly influenced social theory and the remit of sociology itself. His major works dealt with the rationalization, bureaucratization and &apos;disenchantment&apos; associated with the rise of capitalism. Weber was, along with his associate Georg Simmel, a central figure in t</span>
  <span id="freeText2247731681364564938" style="display:none">(Arabic: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/7862079._" rel="nofollow noopener">ماكس فيبر</a>)<br /><br />Maximilian Carl Emil Weber was a German lawyer, politician, historian, sociologist and political economist, who profoundly influenced social theory and the remit of sociology itself. His major works dealt with the rationalization, bureaucratization and 'disenchantment' associated with the rise of capitalism. Weber was, along with his associate Georg Simmel, a central figure in the establishment of methodological antipositivism; presenting sociology as a non-empirical field which must study social action through resolutely subjective means.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2247731681364564938" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

<div class="clear"></div></div></div><div class="bigBoxBottom"></div></div>

  

